definition: to take possession of/to occupy/to take up

sentences.english: Thus, in the ordinary course of warehousing, the temptations to embezzle are strictly limited.
sentences.chinese: 所以在普通仓库的运作中，侵占的诱惑被严格限制了。

sentences.english: The property relationship is the premising constituent of the embezzling crime for its specific character.
sentences.chinese: 具有特定性质的财产关系是侵占罪成立的前提条件。

sentences.english: Also respect the space of other buskers.
sentences.chinese: 也不要侵占其他街头艺人的空间。

sentences.english: The crime of misappropriation is an act of turning a holding into an illegal possession.
sentences.chinese: 侵占罪是易占有为不法所有的行为。
我们还侵占它们的栖息地，铺路盖房子。

sentences.english: More and more of the soil resources were occupied by the rapid urbanization in the Yangtse Delta.
sentences.chinese: 随着城市化的加速发展，越来越多的土壤资源被侵占。

sentences.english: It is always so short, dark gray had encroached on eyes in the sky.
sentences.chinese: 晴天总是那么短，暗灰色早已侵占了眼眸里的天空。

sentences.english: San Marino has been occupied by foreign militaries three times in its history, for only short periods of time.
sentences.chinese: 圣马力诺在历史上有过三次被外国军队短期侵占。

sentences.english: Japan once occupied China's islands in the South China Sea during the Second World War.
sentences.chinese: 日本在二战期间一度侵占中国南海诸岛。

sentences.english: Gradually his capacious chin encroached upon the borders of the white cravat.
sentences.chinese: 他的广阔的下巴逐渐侵占了白领带的边界。

sentences.english: In heavy infestations, the gonad was completely destroyed and replaced by mass of larval treamatodes.
sentences.chinese: 严重感染的宿主，生殖腺完全被侵占并耗尽。

sentences.english: The respect asserted of embezzlement crime.
The prescription of crime of embezzlement is a great step in the criminal legislation.
sentences.chinese: 侵占罪是一种古老且时至今日仍常见多发的犯罪。

sentences.english: This paper analyses several controversy problems on the accusation of occupation.
sentences.chinese: 本文对侵占罪的若干争议问题进行了研析。

sentences.english: Ants are another group of insects that have powerful chemical defenses.
sentences.chinese: 蚂蚁是一群拥正在强大的侵占性化教白器的社会昆虫。
